name: Beedrill V
Attack1Text: Flip 2 coins. This attack does 40 damage for each heads.
Attack2Text: This attack does 50 damage to 1 of your opponent's Pokemon for each of your Beedrill V in play. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokemon.)

name: Hisuian Voltorb
flavorText: An enigmatic Pokemon that happens to bear a resemblance to a Poke Ball. When excited, it discharges the electric current it has stored in its belly, then lets out a great, uproarious laugh.
Attack1Text: You can use this attack only if you go second, and only during your first turn. Choose up to 2 of your Benched Pokemon. For each of those Pokemon, search your deck for a basic Energy card and attach it to that Pokemon. Then, shuffle your deck.

name: Hisuian Electrode
flavorText: The tissue on the surface of its body is curiously similar in composition to an Apricorn. When irritated, this Pokemon lets loose an electric current equal to 20 lightning bolts.
Attack1Text: Draw 3 cards.

name: Scyther
flavorText: The large, wickedly sharp scythes on its forearms are truly fearsome weapons. Prey's attempts to flee are unfailingly thwarted by this Pokemon's nimble motions.

name: Scyther
flavorText: The large, wickedly sharp scythes on its forearms are truly fearsome weapons. Prey's attempts to flee are unfailingly thwarted by this Pokemon's nimble motions.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 30 more damage.

name: Yanma
flavorText: Its frail wings are so thin that one can see clear through them. However, during flight these wings exhibit the power to churn air with force enough to launch a house skyward.

name: Yanmega
flavorText: This six-legged Pokemon is easily capable of transporting an adult in flight. The wings on its tail help it stay balanced.
Attack2Text: If you have more cards in your hand than your opponent, this attack does 80 more damage.

name: Heracross
flavorText: This Pokemon has an unparalleled horn. Heracross itself demonstrates tremendous powerâ€”it's capable of throwing several people trained in the traditional arts of war at once.
Attack2Text: This attack also does 30 damage to 1 of your Benched Pokemon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokemon.)

name: Kricketot
flavorText: When its antennae hit each other, it sounds like the music of a xylophone.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 20 more damage.

name: Kricketune
flavorText: It uses its cutlass-like arms to produce sound, the melody of which varies from individual to individual. It is a worthwhile endeavor to seek out one's favorite tunes.
Ability1Text: Your Grass Pokemon in play, except any Kricketune, get +40 HP. You can't apply more than 1 Swelling Tune Ability at a time.

name: Combee
flavorText: The members of the trio spend all their time together. Each one has a slightly different taste in nectar.
Attack1Text: Search your deck for an Item card, reveal it, and put it into your hand. Then, shuffle your deck.

name: Vespiquen
flavorText: It skillfully commands its grubs in battles with its enemies. The grubs are willing to risk their lives to defend Vespiquen.
Attack1Text: Reveal any number of Sweet Honey cards from your hand. This attack does 60 damage for each card you revealed in this way.

name: Leafeon
flavorText: Cells similar to those of plants have been found in its fur. Its hard tail can fell a large tree with one stroke, and the tail's sharpness exceeds even that of a sword crafted by a master.
Attack1Text: Search your deck for up to 3 basic Energy cards of different types and attach them to your Pokemon in any way you like. Then, shuffle your deck.
Attack2Text: During your next turn, this Pokemon can't attack.

name: Shaymin
flavorText: When the turning of seasons brings the cruel winter to its end and the joyous people give thanks to the heavens, Shaymin appears and covers the withered land with flowers.
Attack1Text: You can use this attack only if you go second, and only during your first turn. Search your deck for up to 3 cards and put them into your hand. Then, shuffle your deck.

name: Petilil
flavorText: The leaves on its head are highly valued for medicinal purposes. Dry the leaves in the sun, boil them, and then drink the bitter decoction for remarkably effective relief from fatigue.
Attack1Text: Switch this Pokemon with 1 of your Benched Pokemon.

name: Hisuian Lilligant
flavorText: I suspect that its well-developed legs are the result of a life spent on mountains covered in deep snow. The scent it exudes from its flower crown heartens those in proximity.
Attack1Text: This attack does 20 damage to each of your opponent's Pokemon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokemon.) Switch this Pokemon with 1 of your Benched Pokemon.

name: Hisuian Lilligant V
Attack1Text: Draw cards until you have 6 cards in your hand.

name: Hisuian Lilligant VSTAR
Ability1Text: During your turn, you may search your deck for up to 5 in any combination of Grass Pokemon and Grass Energy cards, reveal them, and put them into your hand. Then, shuffle your deck. (You can't use more than 1 VSTAR Power in a game.)
Attack1Text: You may put an Energy attached to this Pokemon into your hand. If you do, this attack does 100 more damage.

name: Rowlet
flavorText: Flies noiselessly on delicate wings. It has mastered the art of deftly launching dagger-sharp feathers from those same wings.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 10 more damage.

name: Dartrix
flavorText: Regularly basks in sunlight to gather powerâ€”presumably due to the frigid climate. Nonetheless, the edges of the blade quills set into its wings are keen as ever.

name: Ponyta
flavorText: These Pokemon live in herds out in the grassland. Newborn foals lack their fiery manes, which will develop about an hour after birth.

name: Rapidash
flavorText: This Pokemon can be seen galloping through fields at speeds of up to 150 mph, its fiery mane fluttering in the wind.
Attack2Text: Your opponent's Active Pokemon is now Burned. During your opponent's next turn, that Pokemon can't retreat.

name: Cyndaquil
flavorText: Hails from the Johto region. Though usually curled into a ball due to its timid disposition, it harbors tremendous firepower.
Attack1Text: Search your deck for up to 2 basic Energy cards, reveal them, and put them into your hand. Then, shuffle your deck.

name: Quilava
flavorText: This creature's fur is most mysteriousâ€”it is wholly impervious to the burning touch of flame. Should Quilava turn its back to you, take heed! Such a posture indicates a forthcoming attack.

name: Heatran V
Attack1Text: Your opponent's Active Pokemon is now Burned.
Attack2Text: If you have a Stadium in play, this attack does 90 more damage.

name: Heatran VMAX
Ability1Text: Once during your turn, if you have a Stadium in play, you may heal 50 damage from this Pokemon.
Attack1Text: Your opponent's Active Pokemon is now Burned.

name: Radiant Heatran
flavorText: Boiling blood, like magma, circulates through its body. It makes its dwelling place in volcanic caves.
Attack1Text: This attack does 70 damage for each damage counter on this Pokemon.

name: Psyduck
flavorText: Suffers perpetual headaches. If the agony grows too great, Psyduck's latent power erupts, contrary to Psyduck's intent. Ergo, I am exploring ways to ease the pain.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, heal 10 damage from this Pokemon.

name: Golduck
flavorText: This Pokemon lives in gently flowing rivers. It paddles through the water with its long limbs, putting its graceful swimming skills on display.
Attack2Text: Discard each player's Active Pokemon and all attached cards. (You choose a new Active Pokemon first.)

name: Starmie V
Attack1Text: This attack's damage isn't affected by Weakness or Resistance, or by any effects on your opponent's Active Pokemon.
Attack2Text: This attack does 50 damage for each Energy attached to all of your opponent's Pokemon.

name: Swinub
flavorText: Swinub excels at sniffing out mushrooms buried beneath grass or snow. Since ancient times, the people of Hisui have often relied upon this skill.
Attack2Text: Your opponent's Active Pokemon is now Asleep.

name: Piloswine
flavorText: If it charges at an enemy, the hairs on its back stand up straight. It is very sensitive to sound.
Attack2Text: This attack also does 10 damage to each of your opponent's Benched Pokemon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokemon.)

name: Mamoswine
flavorText: This Pokemon can be spotted in wall paintings from as far back as 10,000 years ago. For a while, it was thought to have gone extinct.
Attack1Text: This attack also does 10 damage to each of your opponent's Benched Pokemon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokemon.)
Attack2Text: Discard an Energy from this Pokemon. During your opponent's next turn, the Defending Pokemon can't attack.

name: Mantine
flavorText: This calm and gentle Pokemon swims gracefully through the sea. After building speed, it can leap out of the water. It is often misidentified as a bird Pokemon due to this behavior.
Attack1Text: Put a Basic Pokemon from either player's discard pile onto that player's Bench.

name: Barboach
flavorText: Makes its home in swamps with murky water. The poor visibility hides this Pokemon from predators, and the slime on its body makes grasping it difficult.

name: Whiscash
flavorText: It makes its nest at the bottom of swamps. It will eat anythingâ€”if it is alive, Whiscash will eat it.
Attack2Text: Flip a coin. If tails, this Pokemon also does 60 damage to itself. If heads, this attack does 60 more damage.

name: Regice
flavorText: With cold air that can reach temperatures as low as âˆ’328 degrees Fahrenheit, Regice instantly freezes any creature that approaches it.
Attack1Text: Search your deck for a Basic Pokemon and put it onto your Bench. Then, shuffle your deck.
Attack2Text: If the Defending Pokemon is a Pokemon V, it can't attack during your opponent's next turn.

name: Glaceon
flavorText: Glaceon is able to lower its body temperature very quickly. It freezes the atmosphere, creating diamond dust that glitters like gems while it flutters and dances around.
Attack1Text: During your opponent's next turn, prevent all damage done to this Pokemon by attacks from Evolution Pokemon.

name: Origin Forme Palkia V
Attack1Text: Search your deck for a Stadium card, reveal it, and put it into your hand. Then, shuffle your deck.
Attack2Text: During your next turn, this Pokemon can't attack.

name: Origin Forme Palkia VSTAR
Ability1Text: During your turn, you may attach up to 3 Water Energy cards from your discard pile to your Water Pokemon in any way you like. (You can't use more than 1 VSTAR Power in a game.)
Attack1Text: This attack does 20 more damage for each Benched Pokemon (both yours and your opponent's).

name: Oshawott
flavorText: This Pokemon from the Unova region uses the shell on its belly as a weapon to cut down its foes. Thus, I've conferred upon this shell the name "scalchop.".

name: Dewott
flavorText: Its exquisite double-scalchop technique is likely the result of daily training, and it can send even masters of the blade fleeing in defeat.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 20 more damage.

name: Hisuian Basculin
flavorText: Though it differs from other Basculin in several respects, including demeanorâ€”this one is gentleâ€”I have categorized it as a regional form given the vast array of shared qualities.
Attack1Text: Search your deck for up to 2 Basic Pokemon and put them onto your Bench. Then, shuffle your deck.

name: Hisuian Basculegion
flavorText: Clads itself in the souls of comrades that perished before fulfilling their goals of journeying upstream. No other species throughout all Hisui's rivers is Basculegion's equal.
Attack1Text: If any of your Pokemon were Knocked Out by damage from an attack from your opponent's Pokemon during their last turn, this attack does 90 more damage, and your opponent's Active Pokemon is now Confused.

name: Keldeo
flavorText: When it is resolute, its body fills with power and it becomes swifter. Its jumps are then too fast to follow.
Attack2Text: This attack does 20 more damage for each of your Benched Pokemon.

name: Radiant Greninja
flavorText: It appears and vanishes with a ninja's grace. It toys with its enemies using swift movements, while slicing them with throwing stars of sharpest water.
Ability1Text: You must discard an Energy card from your hand in order to use this Ability. Once during your turn, you may draw 2 cards.
Attack1Text: Discard 2 Energy from this Pokemon. This attack does 90 damage to 2 of your opponent's Pokemon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokemon.)

name: Bergmite
flavorText: Lives on mountains blanketed in perennial snow. It freezes water vapor in the air to make the ice helmet that it dons for defense.

name: Hisuian Avalugg
flavorText: The armor of ice covering its lower jaw puts steel to shame and can shatter rocks with ease. This Pokemon barrels along steep mountain paths, cleaving through the deep snow.
Ability1Text: This Pokemon takes 30 less damage from attacks (after applying Weakness and Resistance).
Attack1Text: If a Stadium is in play, this attack does 120 more damage. Then, discard that Stadium.

name: Galarian Mr. Rime V
Attack1Text: Search your deck for up to 3 Item cards, reveal them, and put them into your hand. Then, shuffle your deck.
Attack2Text: If this Pokemon has a Pokemon Tool attached, this attack does 90 more damage.

name: Luxray V
Attack1Text: Your opponent reveals their hand. Discard a Trainer card you find there.
Attack2Text: Discard 2 Energy from this Pokemon. Your opponent's Active Pokemon is now Paralyzed.

name: Regieleki
flavorText: This Pokemon is a cluster of electrical energy. It's said that removing the rings on Regieleki's body will unleash the Pokemon's latent power.
Attack1Text: Put a Trainer card from your discard pile into your hand.
Attack2Text: Discard 2 Lightning Energy from this Pokemon. This attack does 120 damage to 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokemon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokemon.)

name: Hisuian Typhlosion
flavorText: Said to purify lost, forsaken souls with its flames and guide them to the afterlife. I believe its form has been influenced by the energy of the sacred mountain towering at Hisui's center.
Ability1Text: You must discard a Psychic Energy card from your hand in order to use this Ability. Once during your turn, you may make your opponent's Active Pokemon Burned and Confused.
Attack1Text: During your opponent's next turn, the Defending Pokemon can't retreat.

name: Hisuian Typhlosion V
Attack1Text: Your opponent's Active Pokemon is now Burned.
Attack2Text: Choose a random card from your opponent's hand. Your opponent reveals that card and shuffles it into their deck.

name: Hisuian Typhlosion VSTAR
Attack1Text: Put 3 damage counters on your opponent's Benched Pokemon in any way you like.
Attack2Text: If your opponent's Active Pokemon has exactly 4 damage counters on it, that Pokemon is Knocked Out. (You can't use more than 1 VSTAR Power in a game.)

name: Togepi
flavorText: This ovate creature is frequently mistaken for a moving egg when encountered out in the fields or in the mountains. Its guileless smile soothes the soul.
Ability1Text: When you play this Pokemon from your hand onto your Bench during your turn, you may heal 10 damage from your Active Pokemon.

name: Togetic
flavorText: They say that it will appear before kindhearted, caring people and shower them with happiness.
Ability1Text: When you play this Pokemon from your hand to evolve 1 of your Pokemon during your turn, you may heal 30 damage from your Active Pokemon.

name: Togekiss
flavorText: These Pokemon are never seen anywhere near conflict or turmoil. In recent times, they've hardly been seen at all.
Ability1Text: When you play this Pokemon from your hand to evolve 1 of your Pokemon during your turn, you may heal 90 damage from your Active Pokemon.

name: Misdreavus
flavorText: It conceals itself in darkness, sending chills up travelers' spines with its childlike weeping. As it observes the frightened travelers with glee, the red orbs upon its chest let off an eerie light.

name: Mismagius
flavorText: Its muttered curses can cause awful headaches or terrifying visions that torment others.
Attack1Text: Your opponent reveals their hand. If they have 4 or more cards in their hand, choose all but 3, and your opponent shuffles the chosen cards into their deck.
Attack2Text: Your opponent's Active Pokemon is now Confused.

name: Ralts
flavorText: Tends to prefer people with a chipper disposition to those who are gloomy, but it has shown no discrimination with regard to age or gender. Needs more research.
Attack1Text: Switch this Pokemon with 1 of your Benched Pokemon.

name: Kirlia
flavorText: If its Trainer becomes happy, it overflows with energy, dancing joyously while spinning about.
Attack1Text: Switch this Pokemon with 1 of your Benched Pokemon.

name: Gallade
flavorText: True to its honorable-warrior image, it uses the blades on its elbows only in defense of something or someone.
Ability1Text: Once during your turn, you may search your deck for a Supporter card, reveal it, and put it into your hand. Then, shuffle your deck.
Attack1Text: Move an Energy from this Pokemon to 1 of your Benched Pokemon.

name: Drifloon
flavorText: Said to lure away young children and carry them off to the afterlife. Some whisper that Drifloon are formed of reincarnated human souls, but these rumors are as yet unconfirmed.
Attack1Text: Flip 3 coins. This attack does 10 damage for each heads.

name: Drifblim
flavorText: Some say this Pokemon is a collection of souls burdened with regrets, silently drifting through the dusk.
Attack1Text: Put 2 damage counters on 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokemon.

name: Uxie
flavorText: It is said that its emergence gave humans the intelligence to improve their quality of life.
Attack1Text: Search your deck for a card and put it into your hand. Then, shuffle your deck.

name: Mesprit
flavorText: It sleeps at the bottom of a lake. Its spirit is said to leave its body to fly on the lake's surface.
Ability1Text: If you have Uxie and Azelf in play, each of your Pokemon has no Weakness.

name: Azelf
flavorText: It is thought that Uxie, Mesprit, and Azelf all came from the same egg.
Attack1Text: Your opponent's Active Pokemon is now Confused.

name: Diancie
flavorText: It can instantly create many diamonds by compressing the carbon in the air between its hands.
Ability1Text: As long as this Pokemon is in the Active Spot, whenever your opponent plays a Supporter card from their hand, prevent all effects of that card done to your Benched Basic Pokemon.
Attack1Text: Draw 2 cards.

name: Wyrdeer
flavorText: The black orbs shine with an uncanny light when the Pokemon is erecting invisible barriers. The fur shed from its beard retains heat well and is a highly useful material for winter clothing.
Ability1Text: Once during your turn, you may draw a card.
Attack1Text: If you have the same number of cards in your hand as your opponent, this attack does 80 more damage.

name: Hisuian Growlithe
flavorText: They patrol their territory in pairs. I believe the igneous rock components in the fur of this species are the result of volcanic activity in its habitat.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, during your opponent's next turn, prevent all damage done to this Pokemon by attacks.

name: Hisuian Arcanine
flavorText: Snaps at its foes with fangs cloaked in blazing flame. Despite its bulk, it deftly feints every which way, leading opponents on a deceptively merry chase as it all but dances around them.
Attack2Text: If this Pokemon has any Fire Energy attached, this attack does 80 more damage, and your opponent's Active Pokemon is now Burned.

name: Machamp V
Attack1Text: If your Benched Pokemon have any damage counters on them, this attack does 50 more damage.

name: Machamp VMAX
Attack1Text: If your Benched Pokemon have any damage counters on them, this attack does 140 more damage.
Attack2Text: During your next turn, this Pokemon can't use G-Max Chi Strike.

name: Sudowoodo
flavorText: Though it pretends to be a tree, it fails to fool even children. To the touch, its body feels more like rock than tree bark. Sudowoodo's extreme aversion to water merits special note.
Ability1Text: If this Pokemon has any damage counters on it, it has no Retreat Cost.
Attack1Text: This Pokemon also does 30 damage to itself.

name: Regirock
flavorText: Every bit of Regirock's body is made of stone. As parts of its body erode, this Pokemon sticks rocks to itself to repair what's been lost.
Attack1Text: Search your deck for a Basic Pokemon and put it onto your Bench. Then, shuffle your deck.
Attack2Text: During your next turn, this Pokemon can't attack.

name: Cranidos
flavorText: Its hard skull is its distinguishing feature. It snapped trees by headbutting them, and then it fed on their ripe berries.
Attack2Text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 40 more damage.

name: Rampardos
flavorText: This ancient Pokemon used headbutts skillfully. Its brain was really small, so some theories suggest that its stupidity led to its extinction.
Attack2Text: If your opponent has 3 or fewer cards in their hand, this attack does nothing.

name: Lucario V
Attack1Text: Discard a Special Energy from your opponent's Active Pokemon.

name: Hippopotas
flavorText: Though large and languid, Hippopotas is difficult to detect due to its tendency to burrow into and lurk beneath the soil. When agitated or excited, it expels sand from its nostrils.

name: Hippowdon
flavorText: Stones can get stuck in the ports on their bodies. Dwebble help dislodge such stones, so Hippowdon look after these Pokemon.
Attack2Text: Discard 2 Energy from this Pokemon.

name: Radiant Hawlucha
flavorText: It drives its opponents to exhaustion with its agile maneuvers, then ends the fight with a flashy finishing move.
Ability1Text: As long as this Pokemon is on your Bench, your Pokemon's attacks do 30 more damage to your opponent's Active Pokemon VMAX (before applying Weakness and Resistance).

name: Hisuian Decidueye
flavorText: The air stored inside the rachises of Decidueye's feathers insulates the Pokemon against Hisui's extreme cold. This is firm proof that evolution can be influenced by environment.
Attack1Text: This attack does 30 damage for each damage counter on your opponent's Active Pokemon.
Attack2Text: This attack does 80 damage to 1 of your opponent's Pokemon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokemon.)

name: Hisuian Decidueye V
Attack1Text: Search your deck for up to 2 cards and put them into your hand. Then, shuffle your deck.
Attack2Text: This attack's damage isn't affected by any effects on your opponent's Active Pokemon.

name: Hisuian Decidueye VSTAR
Ability1Text: During your turn, you may draw cards until you have 8 cards in your hand. (You can't use more than 1 VSTAR Power in a game.)
Attack1Text: You may discard up to 3 Energy cards from your hand. This attack does 30 more damage for each card you discarded in this way.

name: Kleavor
flavorText: A violent creature that fells towering trees with its crude axes and shields itself with hard stone. If one should chance upon this Pokemon in the wilds, one's only recourse is to flee.
Attack1Text: This attack does 30 more damage for each of your opponent's Benched Pokemon.
Attack2Text: This Pokemon also does 50 damage to itself.

name: Kleavor
flavorText: A violent creature that fells towering trees with its crude axes and shields itself with hard stone. If one should chance upon this Pokemon in the wilds, one's only recourse is to flee.
Attack1Text: Flip 2 coins. If both of them are heads, your opponent's Active Pokemon is Knocked Out.
Attack2Text: This Pokemon also does 30 damage to itself.

name: Kleavor V
Attack2Text: Discard an Energy from this Pokemon. If you do, discard an Energy from your opponent's Active Pokemon.

name: Hisuian Qwilfish
flavorText: Fishers detest this troublesome Pokemon because it sprays poison from its spines, getting it everywhere. A different form of Qwilfish lives in other regions.

name: Hisuian Qwilfish
flavorText: Fishers detest this troublesome Pokemon because it sprays poison from its spines, getting it everywhere. A different form of Qwilfish lives in other regions.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin until you get tails. This attack does 10 damage for each heads.

name: Hisuian Overqwil
flavorText: Its lancelike spikes and savage temperament have earned it the nickname "sea fiend." It slurps up poison to nourish itself.
Attack1Text: Your opponent's Active Pokemon is now Poisoned. During Pokemon Checkup, put 5 damage counters on that Pokemon instead of 1.
Attack2Text: During your opponent's next turn, the Defending Pokemon can't retreat.

name: Hisuian Overqwil
flavorText: Its lancelike spikes and savage temperament have earned it the nickname "sea fiend." It slurps up poison to nourish itself.
Attack1Text: If you have at least 3 Darkness Energy in play, this attack does 90 more damage.

name: Hisuian Sneasel
flavorText: Its sturdy, curved claws are ideal for traversing precipitous cliffs. From the tips of these claws drips a venom that infiltrates the nerves of any prey caught in Sneasel's grasp.

name: Hisuian Sneasler
flavorText: Because of Sneasler's virulent poison and daunting physical prowess, no other species could hope to best it on the frozen highlands. Preferring solitude, this species does not form packs.
Ability1Text: As long as this Pokemon is on your Bench, your Active Pokemon's Retreat Cost is ColorlessColorless less.

name: Hisuian Sneasler V
Attack1Text: Your opponent's Active Pokemon is now Poisoned.
Attack2Text: This attack does 80 damage for each Special Condition affecting your opponent's Active Pokemon.

name: Poochyena
flavorText: It has a very tenacious nature. Its acute sense of smell lets it chase a chosen prey without ever losing track.
Attack2Text: This Pokemon also does 10 damage to itself.

name: Mightyena
flavorText: It chases down prey in a pack of around ten. They defeat foes with perfectly coordinated teamwork.
Ability1Text: If your opponent has any Pokemon VMAX in play, this Pokemon's attacks cost ColorlessColorlessColorless less.
Attack1Text: This Pokemon also does 50 damage to itself.

name: Absol
flavorText: Swift as the wind, Absol races through fields and mountains. Its curved, bow-like horn is acutely sensitive to the warning signs of natural disasters.
Attack1Text: This attack does 10 damage to each of your opponent's Pokemon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokemon.)
Attack2Text: If your opponent's Active Pokemon already has any damage counters on it, this attack does 70 more damage.

name: Darkrai V
Attack2Text: Your opponent's Active Pokemon is now Asleep.

name: Darkrai VSTAR
Ability1Text: During your turn, you may put up to 2 Item cards from your discard pile into your hand. (You can't use more than 1 VSTAR Power in a game.)
Attack1Text: This attack does 30 more damage for each Darkness Energy attached to all of your Pokemon.

name: Hisuian Samurott
flavorText: Hard of heart and deft of blade, this rare form of Samurott is a product of the Pokemon's evolution in the region of Hisui. Its turbulent blows crash into foes like ceaseless pounding waves.
Ability1Text: You must discard a card from your hand in order to use this Ability. Once during your turn, you may draw 3 cards.
Attack1Text: This attack does 20 more damage for each Energy attached to all of your Pokemon.

name: Hisuian Samurott V
Attack1Text: Discard up to 2 Pokemon Tools from your opponent's Pokemon.
Attack2Text: Discard an Energy from this Pokemon.

name: Hisuian Samurott VSTAR
Ability1Text: During your turn, you may put 4 damage counters on 1 of your opponent's Pokemon. (You can't use more than 1 VSTAR Power in a game.)
Attack1Text: If your opponent's Active Pokemon already has any damage counters on it, this attack does 110 more damage.

name: Nickit
flavorText: Aided by the soft pads on its feet, it silently raids the food stores of other Pokemon. It survives off its ill-gotten gains.

name: Thievul
flavorText: It secretly marks potential targets with a scent. By following the scent, it stalks its targets and steals from them when they least expect it.
Ability1Text: If your opponent has 2 or fewer Prize cards remaining, whenever your opponent plays a Supporter card from their hand, prevent all effects of that card done to your Benched Pokemon V.

name: Magnemite
flavorText: A bizarre Pokemon with but a single eye embedded in an iron sphere. I suspect this creature levitates due to the magnetism it emits from its arms, which resemble horseshoe-shaped magnets.
Attack1Text: Shuffle up to 3 Metal Energy cards from your discard pile into your deck.

name: Magneton
flavorText: This Pokemon is three Magnemite that have linked together. Magneton sends out powerful radio waves to study its surroundings.
Attack1Text: Your opponent switches their Active Pokemon with 1 of their Benched Pokemon.

name: Magnezone
flavorText: Some say that Magnezone receives signals from space via the antenna on its head and that it's being controlled by some mysterious being.
Ability1Text: Once during your turn, you may look at the top 6 cards of your deck and attach any number of Metal Energy cards you find there to your Pokemon in any way you like. Shuffle the other cards back into your deck.

name: Registeel
flavorText: Registeel's body is made of a strange material that is flexible enough to stretch and shrink but also more durable than any metal.
Attack1Text: Search your deck for a Basic Pokemon and put it onto your Bench. Then, shuffle your deck.
Attack2Text: This attack does 50 less damage for each Colorless in your opponent's Active Pokemon's Retreat Cost.

name: Shieldon
flavorText: Although its fossils can be found in layers of primeval rock, nothing but its face has ever been discovered.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, during your opponent's next turn, prevent all damage from and effects of attacks done to this Pokemon.

name: Bastiodon
flavorText: This Pokemon is from roughly 100 million years ago. Its terrifyingly tough face is harder than steel.
Ability1Text: Your Pokemon take 30 less damage from attacks from your opponent's Pokemon V (after applying Weakness and Resistance).
Attack1Text: This Pokemon also does 30 damage to itself.

name: Bronzor
flavorText: Floats using a mysterious energy. The pattern engraved upon its back is held as sacred and can sometimes be found in imagery from ancient cemeteries and other such timeworn places.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, your opponent's Active Pokemon is now Paralyzed.

name: Bronzong
flavorText: Some believe it to be a deity that summons rain clouds. When angered, it lets out a warning cry that rings out like the tolling of a bell.
Ability1Text: Prevent all damage done to this Pokemon by attacks from your opponent's Fire Pokemon.

name: Origin Forme Dialga V

name: Pawniard
flavorText: It uses river stones to maintain the cutting edges of the blades covering its body. These sharpened blades allow it to bring down opponents.
Attack1Text: This Pokemon also does 10 damage to itself.

name: Bisharp
flavorText: It's accompanied by a large retinue of Pawniard. Bisharp keeps a keen eye on its minions, ensuring none of them even think of double-crossing it.
Attack1Text: This attack does 30 more damage for each damage counter on all of your Benched Pawniard.

name: Garchomp V
Attack2Text: Discard 3 Energy from this Pokemon. This attack does 220 damage to 1 of your opponent's Pokemon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokemon.)

name: Regidrago
flavorText: An academic theory proposes that Regidrago's arms were once the head of an ancient dragon Pokemon. The theory remains unproven.
Ability1Text: Once during your turn, if this Pokemon is in the Active Spot, you may draw cards until you have 4 cards in your hand. You can't use more than 1 Dragon's Hoard Ability each turn.

name: Eevee
evolvesTo: Vaporeon, Jolteon, Flareon, Sylveon, Espeon, Umbreon, Leafeon, Glaceon
flavorText: It has the ability to alter the composition of its body to suit its surrounding environment.
Ability1Text: Once during your turn, when you play a Pokemon from your hand to evolve 1 of your other Eevee, you may search your deck for a card that evolves from this Pokemon and put it onto this Pokemon to evolve it. Then, shuffle your deck.

name: Hoothoot
flavorText: It always stands on one foot. It changes feet so fast, the movement can rarely be seen.
Ability1Text: Basic Energy attached to your Benched Pokemon can't be discarded by an effect of your opponent's Item or Supporter cards.

name: Noctowl

Attack2Text: Discard an Energy from this Pokemon.

flavorText: It licks its paws because of the sweet honey that has soaked into them. It is cunning, stealing into the nests of Combee and taking for itself the honey that the Combee have amassed.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, put an Item card from your discard pile into your hand.

name: Ursaring
flavorText: When the cold season arrives in Hisui, this Pokemon will wander fields and mountains alike in search of its favorite berries. Ursaring's hunger during this time makes it a ferocious danger.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin until you get tails. This attack does 40 damage for each heads.

name: Ursaluna
flavorText: I believe it was Hisui's swampy terrain that gave Ursaluna its burly physique and newfound capacity to manipulate peat at will.
Attack1Text: Put up to 2 cards from your discard pile into your hand.
Attack2Text: Discard 2 Energy from this Pokemon.

name: Stantler
flavorText: Its strangely shaped antlers have the power to bewitch those who see them. Medicine made by grinding up the black orbs from fallen antlers is an effective treatment for insomnia.
Attack1Text: During your opponent's next turn, this Pokemon takes 30 less damage from attacks (after applying Weakness and Resistance).

name: Miltank

Ability1Text: Prevent all damage done to this Pokemon by attacks from your opponent's Pokemon V.
Attack1Text: This attack does 20 more damage for each of your opponent's Benched Pokemon.

name: Glameow

Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, your opponent's Active Pokemon is now Paralyzed.

name: Purugly

Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, your opponent's Active Pokemon is now Paralyzed.

name: Chatot
flavorText: A versatile performer skilled in the imitation of human speech. It is said that older, more experienced Chatot can even understand the meaning of the words they mimic.

Attack2Text: During your opponent's next turn, the Defending Pokemon can't retreat.

name: Regigigas

name: Rufflet
